South Africa's government has finally responded to self-proclaimed prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, absconding the country. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African government has finally responded to self-proclaimed prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, absconding the country. In a statement, the government said they have now started a process to extradite Bushiri. The government says they are going to extradite the Bushiris using the SADC extradition laws. WATCH: Bushiri on his departure from SA The government has also confirmed that Bushiri and his wife Mary did not board the plane with Malawi President Lazarus Chakwera. The Bushiris have contravened their bail conditions as they are not allowed to travel outside SA. Last week, the couple was granted bail of R200,000 each. READ: Bushiri: I'm not running away from my trial They're facing charges of theft, money laundering and fraud in connection with an alleged R100-million investment scheme. Bushiri is adamant he's not trying to evade trial but says he's looking for intervention from his home country.